The paper discusses the use of topic modelling to analyze scientific publications and policy records related to the grand challenge of obesity. This suggests a focus on digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) for the technical aspects of the analysis. The use of policy records also suggests a focus on social and information sciences, such as cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
